%%{ init: { 'theme': 'base', 'sequence': { 'mirrorActors': false } } }%%

sequenceDiagram
    participant C as AI Engineer<br/>(mcp-client.sh)
    participant KC as Keycloak<br/>(OIDC Provider)
    participant E as Envoy Proxy<br/>(team-a namespace)
    participant R as Router<br/>(ext_proc)
    participant A as Authorino<br/>(Wasm plugin → kuadrant-system)
    participant V as Vault<br/>(vault namespace)
    participant B as Broker<br/>(team-a namespace)
    participant S1 as test-server-a1<br/>(team-level credential)
    participant S2 as test-server-a2<br/>(per-user credential)

    Note over C,S2: 1. Token Acquisition

    C->>KC: POST /token<br/>grant_type=password (or device_code)<br/>client_id=mcp-cli<br/>scope=openid groups
    KC-->>C: {"access_token": "eyJ...",<br/>"id_token": "...", "refresh_token": "..."}
    Note over C: Token contains: sub, groups<br/>(e.g. groups: ["team-a-developers"])

    Note over C,S2: 2. Initialize Session

    C->>E: POST /mcp<br/>Authorization: Bearer eyJ...<br/>{"method":"initialize","params":{...}}

    E->>R: ext_proc: headers + body
    Note over R: Method is "initialize"<br/>Leave :authority unchanged<br/>Set x-mcp-method header
    R-->>E: headers unchanged

    Note over E: Wasm plugin calls Authorino
    E->>A: CheckRequest (JWT)
    Note over A: Gateway AuthPolicy (defaults):<br/>1. Validate JWT via Keycloak JWKS<br/>2. Inject X-Mcp-Virtualserver header<br/>   based on groups claim:<br/>   leads → team-a/team-a-lead-tools<br/>   ops → team-a/team-a-ops-tools<br/>   dev → team-a/team-a-dev-tools
    A-->>E: OK + X-Mcp-Virtualserver header

    E->>B: POST /mcp + X-Mcp-Virtualserver
    Note over B: Create session,<br/>store virtualserver binding
    B-->>E: Mcp-Session-Id: eyJ...
    E-->>C: 200 + Mcp-Session-Id header

    Note over C,S2: 3. Discover Tools (tools/list) — filtered by VirtualMCPServer

    C->>E: POST /mcp<br/>Mcp-Session-Id: eyJ...<br/>{"method":"tools/list"}

    E->>R: ext_proc: headers + body
    Note over R: Method is "tools/list"<br/>Leave :authority unchanged
    R-->>E: headers unchanged

    E->>A: CheckRequest (JWT)
    Note over A: Gateway AuthPolicy:<br/>Validate JWT ✓
    A-->>E: OK

    E->>B: POST /mcp
    Note over B: Read VirtualMCPServer from session<br/>Fan out tools/list to all servers<br/>Filter results to only tools<br/>listed in the VirtualMCPServer

    B->>S1: POST /mcp → tools/list
    S1-->>B: 5 tools
    B->>S2: POST /mcp → tools/list
    S2-->>B: 7 tools

    Note over B: VirtualMCPServer filter:<br/>dev → 6 of 12 tools<br/>ops → 6 of 12 tools<br/>leads → all 12 tools

    B-->>E: Filtered tools/list (prefixed names)
    E-->>C: {"tools": [{"name":"test_server_a1_greet"}, ...]}

    Note over C,S2: 4a. Call Tool on server-a1 (team-level Vault credential)

    C->>E: POST /mcp<br/>Mcp-Session-Id: eyJ...<br/>{"method":"tools/call","params":{"name":"test_server_a1_headers"}}

    E->>R: ext_proc: headers + body
    Note over R: 1. Parse tool "test_server_a1_headers"<br/>2. Strip prefix → "headers"<br/>3. Rewrite headers:<br/>   :authority = test-server-a1.mcp.local<br/>   x-mcp-toolname = headers<br/>   x-mcp-servername = team-a/test-server-a1
    R-->>E: Modified headers + body

    Note over E: Wasm plugin calls Authorino<br/>(per-HTTPRoute AuthPolicy for server-a1)
    E->>A: CheckRequest<br/>(host=test-server-a1.mcp.local,<br/>x-mcp-toolname=headers, JWT)

    Note over A: server-a1 AuthPolicy:

    Note over A: Step 1: Validate JWT ✓

    Note over A: Step 2: CEL authorization<br/>groups.exists(g, g == 'team-a-developers')<br/>&& 'headers' in ['greet', 'time', 'headers']<br/>→ ALLOWED ✓

    Note over A: Step 3: Metadata — JWT → Vault token
    A->>V: POST /v1/auth/jwt/login<br/>{"role":"authorino","jwt":"eyJ..."}
    Note over V: Validate JWT via Keycloak JWKS<br/>Check aud: mcp-gateway ✓<br/>Extract sub claim
    V-->>A: {"auth":{"client_token":"hvs.xxx"}}

    Note over A: Step 4: Metadata — read team secret
    A->>V: GET /v1/secret/data/mcp-gateway/teams/team-a-developers<br/>X-Vault-Token: hvs.xxx
    Note over V: CEL selected path based on group:<br/>leads → teams/team-a-leads<br/>ops → teams/team-a-ops<br/>developers → teams/team-a-developers
    V-->>A: {"data":{"data":{"api_key":"team-dev-shared-key-001"}}}

    Note over A: Step 5: Response — inject credential header
    A-->>E: OK + X-Team-Credential: team-dev-shared-key-001

    E->>S1: POST /mcp<br/>X-Team-Credential: team-dev-shared-key-001<br/>{"method":"tools/call","params":{"name":"headers"}}
    Note over S1: Server sees X-Team-Credential<br/>header — can use it to call<br/>downstream APIs on behalf<br/>of the team
    S1-->>E: {"result":{"content":[...]}}
    E-->>C: 200 OK + tool result

    Note over C,S2: 4b. Call Tool on server-a2 (per-user Vault credential)

    C->>E: POST /mcp<br/>{"method":"tools/call","params":{"name":"test_server_a2_headers"}}

    E->>R: ext_proc: headers + body
    Note over R: Strip prefix → "headers"<br/>:authority = test-server-a2.mcp.local<br/>x-mcp-toolname = headers
    R-->>E: Modified headers + body

    E->>A: CheckRequest<br/>(host=test-server-a2.mcp.local,<br/>x-mcp-toolname=headers, JWT)

    Note over A: server-a2 AuthPolicy:

    Note over A: Step 1: Validate JWT ✓

    Note over A: Step 2: CEL authorization<br/>groups.exists(g, g == 'team-a-developers')<br/>&& 'headers' in ['hello_world', 'time', 'headers']<br/>→ ALLOWED ✓

    Note over A: Step 3: Metadata — JWT → Vault token
    A->>V: POST /v1/auth/jwt/login<br/>{"role":"authorino","jwt":"eyJ..."}
    V-->>A: {"auth":{"client_token":"hvs.yyy"}}

    Note over A: Step 4: Metadata — read per-user secret
    A->>V: GET /v1/secret/data/mcp-gateway/users/{sub}<br/>X-Vault-Token: hvs.yyy
    Note over V: Path uses JWT sub claim directly<br/>(Keycloak user UUID)
    V-->>A: {"data":{"data":{"api_key":"dev1-personal-key"}}}

    Note over A: Step 5: Response — inject credential header
    A-->>E: OK + X-User-Credential: dev1-personal-key

    E->>S2: POST /mcp<br/>X-User-Credential: dev1-personal-key<br/>{"method":"tools/call","params":{"name":"headers"}}
    Note over S2: Server sees X-User-Credential<br/>header — can use it to call<br/>identity-bound APIs (e.g. Jira)<br/>on behalf of this specific user
    S2-->>E: {"result":{"content":[...]}}
    E-->>C: 200 OK + tool result

    Note over C,S2: 5. Denied Request (wrong group for tool)

    C->>E: POST /mcp<br/>{"method":"tools/call","params":{"name":"test_server_a1_add_tool"}}

    E->>R: ext_proc: headers + body
    Note over R: Strip prefix → "add_tool"<br/>:authority = test-server-a1.mcp.local<br/>x-mcp-toolname = add_tool
    R-->>E: Modified headers + body

    E->>A: CheckRequest<br/>(x-mcp-toolname=add_tool, JWT)

    Note over A: server-a1 AuthPolicy:<br/>CEL: developers && 'add_tool'<br/>   in ['greet', 'time', 'headers']<br/>→ DENIED ✗<br/><br/>Vault metadata evaluators<br/>are never reached — authorization<br/>fails first.

    A-->>E: DENIED
    E-->>C: 403 Forbidden<br/>{"error":"Forbidden",<br/>"message":"You do not have access to this tool."}
